    "image_with_text_cqHnCf": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_GW6cKf": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>FitAI InStore - The Starter Program</p>",
            "text_font": "heading",
            "text_size": "subtext-custom",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.2,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
            "text_capitalize": false,
            "secondary_color": false,
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_KhVqYe": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The <strong>FitAI InStore</strong> program is available immediately once a retailer has set up the Albert Pro or Zoe Pro scanner software. First, a retailer sends their product feed (usually via Google Shopping) to Aetrex, which is then matched against our SmartLast® database of 3D-scanned footwear. If fewer than 75% of products match the database, Aetrex may scan additional shoes from the retailer’s inventory. Then, FitAI is activated in-store, displaying personalized fit ratings—ranging from Excellent to Poor—based on how a customer’s 3D foot scan compares to each shoe’s internal 3D shape. This initial phase uses a rules-based system for accuracy and clarity.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
            "text_capitalize": false,
